---
title: Cumin-Roasted Carrot and Avocado Salad with Israeli Couscous
description: In this salad, we're roasting carrots with garlic, cumin, and thyme until they’re fragrant and full of concentrated sweetness. Peppery arugula and creamy avocado are then tossed into the mix, resulting in lots of contrasting colors, textures, and flavors. Throw in some pepitas and sour cream for garnish and you’ve got a salad that sings with sunshine-y vibes and lots of veggie wholesomeness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/roasted-carrot-and-avocado-salad-29bf9e82.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/roasted-carrot-and-avocado-salad-1bd428a4.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/roasted-carrot-and-avocado-salad-5835b81d6121bb0b40597162
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 687 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 97 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 19 g
  sodium: 402 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Peel and halve @Carrots{3%unit}, then cut into 2-inch long wedges. Strip leaves from @Thyme{1/4%ounce}. Discard stems. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}. Halve @Lemon{1%unit}.

Squeeze lemon juice into a large #bowl{}. Whisk in garlic, thyme leaves, @Cumin{1%teaspoon}, @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste), @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon}. Add carrot wedges and toss to coat.

Spread carrots onto a #baking sheet{}, keeping some dressing in bowl. Roast until lightly browned, ~{25-30%minutes}. Toss halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a small #pot{} over medium heat. Add @Israeli Couscous{3/4%cup} and toss until slightly fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in 1 1/2 cups @water{1 1/2%cups}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1%unit}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until al dente, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Pit, peel, and dice @Avocado{1%unit}. Toss in bowl with remaining dressing. Toss in roasted carrots, @Arugula{2%ounce}, a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide Israeli couscous between plates. Top with salad. Garnish with @Pepitas{1%ounce} and a dollop of @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}.

> In this salad, we're roasting carrots with garlic, cumin, and thyme until they're
> fragrant and full of concentrated sweetness. Peppery arugula and creamy avocado
> are then tossed into the mix, resulting in lots of contrasting colors, textures,
> and flavors. Throw in some pepitas and sour cream for garnish and you've got a
> salad that sings with sunshine-y vibes and lots of veggie wholesomeness.